==================================================
CURRENT WORK — LeetCode free registry refresh
Date: 2026-04-10
==================================================

==================================================
GOAL
==================================================

Fix registry sync/content issues caused by the old tiny LeetCode manifest:

1. expand the LeetCode problem pool
2. include only free LeetCode problems
3. avoid syncing nil/null starter_code values
4. keep the registry metadata-only
5. make the refresh repeatable

==================================================
WHAT CHANGED
==================================================

1. LEETCODE PROVIDER MANIFEST

  Updated:
    registry/providers/leetcode.json

  Source:
    LeetCode public GraphQL problemset metadata

  Current fetched totals:
    total questions: 3893
    free questions: 3131
    paid questions: 762

  The manifest now contains 3131 free LeetCode problems.

  Each entry includes:
    provider
    external_id
    slug
    title
    difficulty
    tags
    pattern_tags
    source_url
    estimated_time
    starter_code
    version

  It does NOT include:
    problem statements
    editorials
    solutions
    test cases
    paid-only problem entries

2. REGISTRY INDEX

  Updated:
    registry/index.json

  New version:
    2026-04-10-leetcode-free

  LeetCode checksum:
    sha256:133b1316260bd22cf0fb843b5e839b9ed84fc42a270ad74113d319e938b352c5

3. STARTER CODE SYNC HARDENING

  Updated:
    internal/infrastructure/postgres/registry.go

  UpsertFromManifest now converts nil StarterCode maps to an empty map before
  marshaling, so missing starter_code syncs as {} instead of JSON null.

4. REFRESH SCRIPT

  Added:
    scripts/update_leetcode_registry.sh
    scripts/update_leetcode_registry.mjs

  The script:
    - pages LeetCode metadata 100 questions at a time
    - filters paidOnly == false
    - fetches Python/Go starter snippets in GraphQL batches
    - generates registry/providers/leetcode.json
    - computes the provider manifest sha256
    - updates registry/index.json

  Note:
    The listing endpoint returns both free and paid-only metadata in the paged
    response. The generated local registry filters out paid-only entries and
    persists only free problems.

==================================================
STARTER CODE STATUS
==================================================

After adding the starter-code detail fetch:

  free problems: 3131
  with any Python/Go starter code: 2970
  with Python starter code: 2970
  with Go starter code: 2968
  without Python/Go starter code: 161

The entries without Python/Go starter code are mostly non-algorithm LeetCode
categories such as Database and Shell, or entries where LeetCode does not expose
the requested snippets.

==================================================
TEST CASE STATUS
==================================================

Bulk LeetCode test cases are still not imported.

Reasons:
  - LeetCode's public question detail metadata exposes exampleTestcases as
    example inputs, not expected outputs suitable for local judging.
  - Fetching/copying full statement examples would turn the registry into more
    than metadata.
  - The current sandbox executes whole programs with stdin, while LeetCode
    starter snippets are function/class templates. A harness layer is needed
    before LeetCode-style examples can be judged correctly.

Curated local problems can still provide test cases through:
  POST /api/problems/contribute

==================================================
DESIGN DECISIONS
==================================================

Bulk-imported LeetCode entries use LeetCode's Python/Go starter snippets when
available. Entries without Python/Go snippets use starter_code: {}.

Reason:
  This gives algorithm problems useful editor buffers while still allowing the
  Neovim plugin to fall back to local templates for Database/Shell/unsupported
  entries.

Pattern tags currently mirror LeetCode topic tag slugs.

Reason:
  This preserves useful metadata now without inventing a lossy mapping layer.
  A later pass can map topic tags into higher-level training patterns.
